\b Remediation Matrix\b0\par
\par
This Word-compatible tracking document is intended for team use after manual assessment findings are confirmed.\par
\par
\b Instructions\b0\par
1. Assign an owner for each confirmed gap.\par
2. Set target dates and track status weekly.\par
3. Attach evidence references when remediation is completed.\par
\par
\b AC-2 Account Management\b0\par
Gap: No authenticated user model; API defaults to anonymous user IDs.\par
Risk: Unauthorized or untraceable access.\par
Priority: Critical.\par
Owner: ____________________\par
Target Date: ____________________\par
Status: ____________________\par
Planned Remediation: Implement centralized authentication, require unique user identity on protected endpoints, add RBAC, and establish account lifecycle workflow.\par
Evidence to Produce: IAM design, access review evidence, deprovisioning records.\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
\par
